Lumina is a lightweight [[desktop environment]], free of dbus and *kit, designed to require as few system dependencies/requirements as possible.

== Installation ==

{{RootCmd|emerge --ask x11-wm/lumina}}

== Running Lumina ==

Lumina provides its own replacement for {{c|[[Xorg/Guide#Using_startx|startx]]}} to be started from console.

{{Cmd|start-lumina-desktop}}

Alternatively it can be added to the {{Path|~./xinitrc}} file for being started via {{c|[[Xorg/Guide#Using_startx|startx]]}} or a [[display manager]]

{{FileBox|filename=~/.xinitrc|1=
# https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/X_resources#Adding_to_xinitrc
[[ -f ~/.Xresources ]] && xrdb -merge -I$HOME ~/.Xresources

exec start-lumina-desktop}}

or to {{Path|/etc/env.d/90xsession}} for users not having an {{Path|~./xinitrc}} file:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/env.d/90xsession|1=
XSESSION="lumina"}}

